                    </div>
                    <span>I got this book as a gift from my wife and I love it.
<br />
<br />I am a Mac addict and I have been using Mac for ever. I love this book because it gives very interesting stories about the Mac from a non-techy point of view.
<br />
<br />I believe this is a great gift for someone who loves his Mac. However, it may be a little boring for someone who does not have a true passion for his Mac.
<br />
<br />Enjoy your Mac.
<br />
<br />Donald</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Artistic and enlightening</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
                      /
                      <span>2</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-12-15</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Few products acquire such fierce loyalty like the Mac.  Fewer products inspire the creative juices and desire to "think different" than the Mac does.  If you've just sighed or harrumphed quietly to yourself (you know who you are) then you need to a) lighten up and b) peruse the pages of this book...  Come over to the Mac side...  It'll be our little secret...  =)
<br />
<br />Beautifully creative and artistic, full color pages end to end.  The book reveals in "coffee table format" a little history, a number of confessions, and plenty of portraiture from the birth of the Mac to the present day.  My favorite chapter discusses the "Fantasy Macs".  Mac devotees all over the world design and publish incredibly innovative and fanciful images of imaginary (and sometimes not so imaginary) Macs.
<br />
<br />A must have for the True Mac user.  For the rest, a little taste of what you've been missing out on for the last twenty years.</span>
                  
              
